Oh. Jesus. God.

42:28.715 --> 42:31.426
Yeah, I really know how to pick one
or what?

42:31.468 --> 42:33.720
The judge said if he threats anyone
he goes back to jail.

42:33.804 --> 42:36.139
Back to jail? What jail?

42:36.390 --> 42:39.142
Prison, actually.
Walla Walla.

42:41.854 --> 42:43.605
That's where Forster is.

42:45.941 --> 42:46.859
Come on, let's go.

42:47.651 --> 42:49.528
Special Agent Parks.

42:49.695 --> 42:50.821
<i>Frank, it's Jack.</i>

42:50.946 --> 42:54.366
I'm at the university campus.
We got a problem here.

42:54.449 --> 42:57.911
Someone attacked one of my students and
tried to knock her out with Halothane.

42:58.161 --> 43:01.582
<i>- That's the Seattle slayer.
- I know, hold on.</i>

43:01.832 --> 43:03.125
Give me a second.

43:04.251 --> 43:08.755
Yeah. There's a security guard
on this campus, his name is D'Franco.

43:08.964 --> 43:10.924
I don't like him.
He's suspicious.

43:11.175 --> 43:13.135
I want you to take him in
for questioning, okay?

43:13.343 --> 43:15.971
Also get a warrant
and search his place.

43:16.054 --> 43:17.139
Jesus Christ, Jack.

43:17.222 --> 43:19.975
You know I can't just get a warrant
without sufficient grounds.

43:20.184 --> 43:22.186
Just get a warrant, Frank,
come on.

43:22.269 --> 43:23.979
<i>Do you think he is the slayer?</i>

43:24.479 --> 43:27.441
<i>- To link Forster on the outside?
- It's possible.</i>

43:27.691 --> 43:31.486
Listen, I checked the names
that Shelley, of the students.

43:31.778 --> 43:35.490
And there's no record of Lauren Douglas,
Kim Cummings or Sara Pollard...

43:35.699 --> 43:36.617
but you gonna love this.

43:36.867 --> 43:41.496
<i>Mike Stempt visit Forster four times
over the last six weeks.</i>

43:41.997 --> 43:43.832
Mike Stempt. What was his reason?

43:44.249 --> 43:46.251
<i>Research.
He had written permission.</i>

43:46.460 --> 43:48.504
<i>No, no, no.
I didn't give him any permission.</i>

43:48.754 --> 43:50.172
Written or otherwise.

43:50.422 --> 43:53.592
Well, it's your signature, Jack.
I got a copy right here.

43:54.843 --> 43:56.386
Hold on.
That... Hold on a second.

43:56.637 --> 43:58.722
That ex boyfriend of yours.
What is his name?

43:58.931 --> 44:00.349
Guy LaForge.

44:00.599 --> 44:03.268
Run a check on a parole
named Guy LaForge.

44:03.477 --> 44:06.271
He served time at Walla Walla
with Forster.

44:06.605 --> 44:09.107
And I'll call you back
when I get to my apartment.

44:09.441 --> 44:10.859
All right.

44:12.528 --> 44:14.112
Do you think that Frank is working
with Forster?

44:14.321 --> 44:15.614
<i>Someone is.</i>

44:15.781 --> 44:17.699
- I got you Johnson.
- Yeah.

44:18.408 --> 44:20.327
They've found a backpack
in your lecture hall.

44:20.702 --> 44:22.204
What? With a bomb in it?

44:22.663 --> 44:26.542
No. A photo, dynamite,
and a time with a note addressed to you.

44:26.750 --> 44:27.668
What did it say?

44:27.876 --> 44:29.086
Tic-tac.

44:30.754 --> 44:31.797
What does it mean, Jack?

44:32.089 --> 44:33.674
I call you back.

44:58.574 --> 45:00.242
- You are okay?
- Yeah.

45:00.492 --> 45:02.244
What the hell was that?

45:03.787 --> 45:05.956
Probably somebody
trying to scare us.

45:06.123 --> 45:08.584
Who do you think would do
something like that?

45:09.543 --> 45:12.045
Does your boyfriend drive
a motorcycle?

45:12.296 --> 45:13.589
Yeah.

45:13.797 --> 45:16.383
Except he's not my boyfriend
anymore.

45:17.134 --> 45:17.885
Yeah.

45:18.135 --> 45:20.971
<i>How does it feel to know
you won't live through another night?</i>

45:21.138 --> 45:22.306
<i>56 minutes.</i>

45:23.056 --> 45:24.600
<i>Tic-tac, doc.</i>

45:26.351 --> 45:27.561
Let's go.

46:15.442 --> 46:17.027
Guy LaForge.

46:17.486 --> 46:19.363
He isn't a boyfriend, is he?

46:21.365 --> 46:24.868
The only thing that got me out of Texas
was my books marks.

46:25.994 --> 46:29.414
And when I left for college,
I had that, but not much else.

46:29.498 --> 46:33.001
So I tried to fit in.
I drank too much.

46:34.711 --> 46:36.255
Thought too little.

46:36.922 --> 46:38.674
And I met Guy.

46:42.219 --> 46:44.221
And he was this English...

46:44.763 --> 46:47.349
working class rock star
wanna be.

46:47.432 --> 46:49.309
And I fell for him.

46:50.561 --> 46:52.396
And I married him...

46:52.479 --> 46:54.064
when I graduated.

46:55.566 --> 46:59.695
He didn't take to well to my aspirations
for higher education.

47:00.153 --> 47:03.782
In fact he didn't really want me to
leave the house. And when I disobeyed...

47:03.991 --> 47:06.910
he got filthy drunk
and he beat me.

47:07.411 --> 47:09.746
That's when he got arrested
and I divorced him.

47:09.997 --> 47:13.000
I've been trying to make up
for lost time ever since.

47:18.422 --> 47:21.550
- You know, Forster is trying to kill me.
- Forster is in prison.

47:21.842 --> 47:24.511
Yeah, I know. He's got someone
on the outside trying to...

47:25.470 --> 47:27.097
to do the job.

47:30.225 --> 47:31.768
He's gonna kill me.

47:33.353 --> 47:35.272
If I don't get him first.

47:40.861 --> 47:43.405
Whoever is working with Forster
must be close to you.

47:43.572 --> 47:46.950
- A friend even.
- I don't have many friends.

47:47.159 --> 47:48.243
That's a plus.

47:48.327 --> 47:51.580
It's a real pleasure to look at everyone
you know as your would be murderer.

47:51.788 --> 47:54.249
Paranoia is a normal state of mind,
huh?

47:55.918 --> 47:57.002
Where is Errol?

47:57.085 --> 47:59.963
I don't know. I'm a temp.
The agency sent me.

48:00.589 --> 48:02.090
Dr. Gramm?

48:02.549 --> 48:04.301
There's a package for you.

48:07.804 --> 48:09.306
How did you know my name?

48:09.473 --> 48:12.017
I don't.
It was a question.

48:13.644 --> 48:14.811
Yeah.

48:15.687 --> 48:18.106
- There's no returning address on this?
- No.

48:19.691 --> 48:21.109
Who delivered it?

48:21.318 --> 48:24.446
A carrier. But there was
another person here at the same time...

48:24.613 --> 48:26.782
- Iooking for you.
- Who?

48:27.032 --> 48:29.284
- What was his name?
- No, I didn't get it.

48:29.451 --> 48:31.828
When he walked in I was on the phone
with the plumber.

48:31.912 --> 48:37.167
- He said he would be right back.
- Okay.

48:37.251 --> 48:38.836
You wanna me pull
the surveillance tapes?

48:38.919 --> 48:41.421
That shouldn't take more than an hour
to get someone up here with the keys.

48:43.674 --> 48:45.384
- I don't have an hour.
- No?

48:45.634 --> 48:50.430
Hey, you know, he was also wearing
leathers. He had a motorcycle helmet.

48:50.639 --> 48:52.808
That's Guy. He was here.

48:54.434 --> 48:57.521
If he comes back,
don't send him up to my apartment.

48:58.188 --> 48:59.439
Yeah.

49:00.315 --> 49:02.192
- Hi, Dr. Gramm.
- Hi, Eva.

49:11.159 --> 49:13.328
How did Guy know
we're going to be here?

49:13.537 --> 49:15.330
How does even know
where you live?

49:15.622 --> 49:17.499
Oh, Walther P99.

49:17.708 --> 49:19.877
That would blow a hole
through anything.

49:21.587 --> 49:23.839
What?
I grew up around guns.

49:24.089 --> 49:27.342
Maybe he didn't know I was gonna
be here, maybe that's why he showed up.

49:28.218 --> 49:31.305
I'll verify where he went after
the party last night.

49:32.556 --> 49:35.225
<i>There's a Lauren Douglas to see you.
Should I send her up?</i>

49:35.893 --> 49:37.269
Okay, send her up.

49:40.355 --> 49:42.316
He got that right, didn't he?

49:42.649 --> 49:44.109
Hey, what's that?

49:44.776 --> 49:46.028
This?

49:46.570 --> 49:48.322
It's a chemical detector.

49:48.989 --> 49:52.993
It sniffs out vapors.
Custom agencies are using it.

49:53.744 --> 49:54.995
And?

50:00.584 --> 50:02.044
It's not a bomb.

50:02.503 --> 50:03.504
That's good.

50:04.254 --> 50:05.380
Yeah.

50:17.559 --> 50:19.061
- Hi.
- Hi.

50:19.144 --> 50:22.064
- Are you okay?
- Yeah. I'm better, thank you.

50:24.608 --> 50:27.444
- What do you have?
- I went to see Shelley like you said.

50:27.528 --> 50:30.489
She tried to fax you over some papers,
but the machine was down.

50:30.864 --> 50:34.201
So I said I'd bring the risk assessment
profiles over myself.

50:35.118 --> 50:37.663
I didn't know you had company.

50:38.038 --> 50:41.250
Dale told me how good you're with her
when her dad died.

50:42.000 --> 50:43.794
She was so grateful.

50:45.212 --> 50:46.797
Dr. Gramm?

50:46.964 --> 50:48.006
Yeah?

50:48.215 --> 50:50.801
If there's anything I can do
to help you find Dale's murderer...

50:50.884 --> 50:53.470
- will you let me know?
- Of course, yes.

50:54.596 --> 50:55.806
Thank you.

50:56.974 --> 50:59.560
Can I call you a cab
or something?

50:59.977 --> 51:02.354
No, Mike is gonna give me
a ride.

51:02.646 --> 51:03.856
- Okay.
- Thanks for these...

51:04.189 --> 51:05.315
Bye.

51:09.528 --> 51:11.864
All those people
have threatened you?

51:12.030 --> 51:14.825
Well, you know,
it comes with the territory.

51:15.450 --> 51:17.744
How come you never mention that
in class?

51:18.996 --> 51:22.666
How many students end up going
into this field anyway?

51:23.166 --> 51:26.587
Not very many
with you booting all of them.

51:27.671 --> 51:28.505
Yeah.

51:37.181 --> 51:39.266
Can I ask you
a personal question?

51:39.474 --> 51:40.642
No.

51:41.852 --> 51:43.270
How come you never
got married?

51:43.770 --> 51:45.814
I mean,
you're a pretty good prospect.

51:46.607 --> 51:48.483
You obviously make a shit load
of money.

51:48.567 --> 51:49.651
Why would I get married?

51:49.902 --> 51:52.112
I'm a target for any nut
with a grudge.

51:54.406 --> 51:56.658
I can't afford emotional
attachments.

51:56.909 --> 51:58.243
Yeah, but don't you want kids?

51:58.702 --> 52:00.204
Don't you want a family?

52:00.454 --> 52:02.039
I'm too old for kids.

52:05.209 --> 52:07.586
You're too young for me, Kim.

52:10.714 --> 52:14.593
If you want me to leave, Jack, all
you've got to do is say it and I'm gone.

52:14.885 --> 52:16.803
No, I don't want you to leave.

52:17.221 --> 52:18.680
I need you, Kim.

52:18.764 --> 52:20.891
You are smart
and you are important to me.

52:20.974 --> 52:22.809
Really, you are.

52:25.479 --> 52:26.688
Okay.

52:45.374 --> 52:47.376
<i>- Yeah.
- Jack, it's Shelley.</i>

52:47.417 --> 52:48.919
What the hell happened to you?
Where have you been

52:49.127 --> 52:52.172
Making calls for you, four lines
simultaneously. The fax is down.

52:52.214 --> 52:54.591
<i>I know, Lauren Douglas came over
and brought some papers with her.</i>

52:54.675 --> 52:56.510
Jack, you better turn on MS-NBC.

52:56.677 --> 52:57.427
Why?

52:57.511 --> 53:00.180
Forster got a judge to grant
his request for an interview.

53:00.347 --> 53:01.306
<i>He's on, live.</i>

53:01.515 --> 53:04.059
<i>This is gonna heat things up</i>

53:03.700 --> 53:04.784
<i>When looking for a home...</i>

53:04.868 --> 53:07.245
<i>a real estate agent is really important
in you life. You need someone...</i>

53:09.242 --> 53:10.660
Shelley. Listen to me.

53:10.869 --> 53:14.164
I want you to send some of the boys
to my apartment, all right?

53:14.372 --> 53:17.917
There may be someone down at my lobby
in biker leathers when they get there.

53:18.001 --> 53:18.960
Okay?

53:19.627 --> 53:22.422
<i>- You got a name?
- Yes, his name is Guy LaForge.</i>

53:22.797 --> 53:27.177
Put a photo
on the FBI wire, okay?

53:27.427 --> 53:29.554
<i>If you are not granted
another stay of the execution...</i>

53:29.804 --> 53:31.139
<i>are you prepared to die?</i>

53:31.389 --> 53:32.348
You want me to call the police?

53:32.432 --> 53:35.351
No, no, let Frank handle it.
He'll know what to do.

53:35.435 --> 53:37.604
<i>As prepared as any man can be
to pay for something he didn't do.</i>

53:37.687 --> 53:38.772
Listen.

53:38.980 --> 53:42.567
You didn't message over a package
to my apartment, did you?

53:42.817 --> 53:43.443
No.

53:43.693 --> 53:46.112
<i>There is a lot of people out there
that believe in your innocence.</i>

53:46.321 --> 53:47.113
<i>And I'm grateful.</i>

53:47.322 --> 53:48.615
You know anyone that might have?

53:48.823 --> 53:50.617
<i>- No.
- I'm grateful for their prayers.</i>

53:50.825 --> 53:53.036
<i>- Everything goes to your office.
- And support.</i>

53:53.119 --> 53:54.996
What about Pollard.
Find anything on her?

53:55.830 --> 53:57.374
You didn't actually paid her,
did you, Jack?

53:57.582 --> 54:00.251
- Pay her, what do you mean?
- She works for a escort service.

54:00.460 --> 54:01.920
Escort service?

54:02.212 --> 54:03.922
<i>You didn't know?</i>

54:04.339 --> 54:05.590
No, I didn't know.

54:08.009 --> 54:11.638
What? She told me she was a lawyer.
A student lawyer.

54:12.138 --> 54:14.140
<i>What are your thoughts
this time?</i>

54:14.224 --> 54:16.768
<i>Well, Stephanie, that's one thing
I don't have a lot of...</i>

54:17.102 --> 54:18.978
You got a number for her?

54:20.313 --> 54:21.648
<i>Yeah, a phone number
and the address.</i>

54:21.815 --> 54:23.191
I know the address.

54:23.942 --> 54:24.943
Let me have the number.

54:25.151 --> 54:27.278
<i>If Dr. Gramm was with us right now,
what would you say to him?</i>

54:27.362 --> 54:30.156
<i>555-1352.</i>

54:30.365 --> 54:32.158
<i>He knows that I didn't do this.</i>

54:32.867 --> 54:33.827
<i>- There's only one...
- Thanks.</i>

54:33.910 --> 54:37.997
<i>Other person in this world
who knows I've been framed.</i>

54:38.248 --> 54:42.377
<i>That it was a set up.
That I'm totally innocent.</i>

54:43.044 --> 54:47.173
<i>And that would be the forensic
psychiatric Dr. Jack Gramm.</i>

54:48.049 --> 54:51.219
<i>I guess what I'd say to Jack Gramm...
I'd say, "Why me"?</i>

54:53.096 --> 54:56.141
<i>I understand that you've suffered
a great loss with your sister.</i>

54:56.599 --> 54:59.060
<i>I feel your pain, Dr. Gramm.</i>

54:59.519 --> 55:01.312
<i>- Pick it up, damn it.
- But that doesn't exonerate you...</i>

55:01.396 --> 55:05.859
<i>from false accusing me of things that
you know I did not, could not have done.</i>

55:05.942 --> 55:07.152
Pick up, Sara.

55:07.902 --> 55:10.447
<i>If I can be convicted
of this voodoo forensic science...</i>

55:10.530 --> 55:12.032
<i>think about it... Who is safe?</i>

55:15.285 --> 55:16.453
Shelley?

55:16.703 --> 55:18.955
Shelley?
I want you to get MS-NBC.

55:19.039 --> 55:21.958
<i>- I want to talk to that son-of-bitch.
- I would be the last.</i>

55:22.208 --> 55:23.710
Jack, I really don't think
that's a good idea.

55:24.002 --> 55:27.130
It's a good idea. Just get them
and when you get them call me back, OK?

55:27.714 --> 55:30.884
<i>But I find hard to believe that
Dr. Jack Gramm can be out there...</i>

55:31.217 --> 55:34.804
<i>psycho battling innocent people
into the death chamber.</i>

55:35.305 --> 55:37.182
<i>Who is the murder now, Jack?</i>

55:38.058 --> 55:38.892
Yeah?

55:39.476 --> 55:40.894
<i>Who is the murder now?</i>

55:41.269 --> 55:42.729
<i>Jack?</i>

55:43.021 --> 55:45.356
We got D'Franco in custody.

55:45.607 --> 55:47.108
I got the warrant.

55:47.317 --> 55:49.444
The guys are on the way
over to his place.

55:49.527 --> 55:51.279
Did he say anything about Forster?

55:51.488 --> 55:53.448
<i>A quite bit, but nothing useful.</i>

55:53.948 --> 55:55.200
What about Guy LaForge?

55:55.492 --> 55:58.745
He hasn't checked in with
his parole office in six weeks.

55:58.995 --> 56:02.123
Well, he was at my apartment building
less than an hour ago.

56:02.332 --> 56:04.000
And he said he's coming back.

56:05.001 --> 56:06.753
Listen, Frank.

56:06.961 --> 56:09.089
I got a call
a little while ago...

56:09.297 --> 56:11.174
saying I have 88 minutes
to live.

56:11.466 --> 56:14.177
Jesus, Jack.
Why 88 minutes?

56:19.432 --> 56:21.017
I don't know.

56:22.310 --> 56:24.437
<i>You have any idea
who this caller is?</i>

56:27.315 --> 56:31.945
You better find Guy LaForge
before he gets here, okay?

56:32.028 --> 56:33.988
Listen, let me call you back.

56:34.155 --> 56:35.240
Jack?

56:36.324 --> 56:37.033
Shit.

56:54.676 --> 56:55.802
<i>Mom.</i>

56:56.052 --> 56:57.595
<i>Dad.</i>

56:57.846 --> 56:59.055
<i>Jack.</i>

56:59.764 --> 57:01.182
<i>There's someone in here.</i>

57:01.349 --> 57:03.309
<i>And he wants to talk to you.</i>

57:03.935 --> 57:05.353
<i>Where are you?</i>

57:05.437 --> 57:07.564
<i>Please, come home quickly!</i>

57:07.814 --> 57:09.733
<i>I'm here with a man.</i>

57:10.108 --> 57:12.193
<i>It is not what
you want me to say...</i>

57:13.027 --> 57:16.823
<i>Jack, come here now!
Help me. Help me.</i>

57:29.919 --> 57:31.504
Jack, what is that?

57:33.048 --> 57:34.466
My sister.

57:35.216 --> 57:36.718
Oh, my God!

57:38.219 --> 57:41.097
That's horrible.
Who would send that to you?

57:43.725 --> 57:46.352
There's only two copies
of this tape in the world.

57:46.436 --> 57:47.812
One is...

57:48.229 --> 57:51.024
Iocked up in custody of NYPD.

57:51.066 --> 57:52.442
And the other...

57:54.819 --> 57:57.864
is in a restricted access room...

57:58.031 --> 58:00.116
in my office file cabinet...

58:01.826 --> 58:04.371
with the highest
security measures.

58:04.412 --> 58:06.247
So you're thinking it was stolen.

58:06.664 --> 58:08.625
Of course it was stolen.

58:15.757 --> 58:17.133
You think I stole it?

58:18.885 --> 58:20.595
You think I stole it?

58:20.804 --> 58:22.680
You left the bar yesterday night
with Dale.

58:22.764 --> 58:26.017
One of the last people to see
her alive. Maybe the last.

58:26.226 --> 58:30.480
Jack, you think I stole the tape
and killed Dale?

58:30.647 --> 58:32.023
Have you lost your mind?

58:32.273 --> 58:35.110
I don't have clearance
to your restricted access room.

58:35.193 --> 58:37.195
Why Guy LaForge was at the bar
last night?

58:39.322 --> 58:41.324
<i>He was trying to protect me.</i>

58:41.700 --> 58:42.951
<i>From what?</i>

58:44.411 --> 58:47.038
- From you.
- From me? He knows about me?

58:47.205 --> 58:48.707
- Yes.
- What does he know about me?

58:48.957 --> 58:52.085
He knows I have
a silly girlish crush on you.

58:53.169 --> 58:54.754
Jack. Hold on a second.

58:54.879 --> 58:57.716
I just got an email
from Mike Stempt, okay?

58:57.966 --> 59:00.760
He saw Guy at Darby's Club
last night.

59:00.969 --> 59:03.430
When Mike left at 3 am,
Guy was still sitting there...

59:03.471 --> 59:05.515
and they've bounced a beer
until 6 am.

59:05.974 --> 59:09.060
So there's no way that Guy
could have killed Dale Morris.

59:17.610 --> 59:20.447
<i>- Yeah?
- Did you listen to the tape, Dr. Gramm?</i>

59:20.613 --> 59:23.033
<i>Why did you leave the little Katie
all alone?</i>

59:23.199 --> 59:24.659
<i>Why, Dr. Gramm?</i>

59:24.826 --> 59:29.122
<i>She'd still be alive today if you
hadn't left her all alone to die.</i>

59:30.123 --> 59:33.960
<i>Now it's your turn.
In a glaze of glory!</i>

59:34.294 --> 59:35.754
