01:38:24.666 --> 01:38:27.460
Dr. Gramm, I'm flattered
with your imagination.

01:38:28.169 --> 01:38:29.295
But you're grasping in straw.

01:38:29.462 --> 01:38:32.173
She becomes a student of mine,
no less...

01:38:32.465 --> 01:38:35.635
you keep her on the appeal process,
but she's still your lawyer...

01:38:35.719 --> 01:38:38.138
so she has unlimited access
to you...

01:38:38.346 --> 01:38:41.516
so you can plan
your copy cat murders together.

01:38:41.850 --> 01:38:44.018
And then you can get a new trial.

01:38:44.102 --> 01:38:46.646
And live happily ever after.
Isn't that the case?

01:38:46.813 --> 01:38:50.066
Dr. Gramm, I want you to listen
very closely...

01:38:50.859 --> 01:38:52.902
because when I get out of here...

01:38:53.528 --> 01:38:55.488
I'm gonna go out and
have a nice meal...

01:38:56.156 --> 01:38:57.866
stop by your grave...

01:38:58.700 --> 01:39:00.493
and piss all over it.

01:39:01.870 --> 01:39:04.372
Now, please, put my angelical attorney
on the phone.

01:39:04.622 --> 01:39:05.331
She's dead.

01:39:06.583 --> 01:39:08.376
<i>It's over, Forster.</i>

01:39:08.626 --> 01:39:10.503
<i>Except for the clock,
that goes tic-tac.</i>

01:39:10.754 --> 01:39:13.465
Tic-tac.
You got 12 hours to live.

01:39:47.290 --> 01:39:49.209
All right, fellows...

01:39:55.298 --> 01:39:57.217
- How is Lynn Johnson?
- Well...

01:39:57.467 --> 01:40:02.013
She just threw out of the house.
She didn't want me to be late for class.

01:40:02.430 --> 01:40:04.349
Jack, I have to ask you
something.

01:40:04.432 --> 01:40:07.394
Was Lydia telling the truth?
Did you coach Janie?

01:40:07.769 --> 01:40:11.356
You believe Forster killed those people?
All those people?

01:40:11.481 --> 01:40:14.275
- Yes.
- Janie's sister and everybody?

01:40:14.359 --> 01:40:16.319
- Yes.
- Beyond reasonable doubt?

01:40:16.528 --> 01:40:19.906
- Absolutely.
- What would you have done in my shoes?

01:40:21.449 --> 01:40:22.617
Don't answer it.

01:40:22.826 --> 01:40:24.077
Think about it.

01:40:24.452 --> 01:40:25.704
Justice...

01:40:26.287 --> 01:40:27.580
and truth.

01:40:29.124 --> 01:40:30.750
Where do they intersect?

01:40:47.684 --> 01:40:48.601
Hi.

01:40:53.940 --> 01:40:55.358
Hello, everyone.

01:41:00.572 --> 01:41:02.407
John Forster is dead.

01:41:04.868 --> 01:41:07.829
<i>His execution is not a cause...</i>

01:41:08.997 --> 01:41:10.457
<i>for celebration.</i>

01:41:11.249 --> 01:41:13.668
<i>Nor is a vindication.</i>

01:41:14.335 --> 01:41:17.172
<i>It is a chapter...</i>

01:41:18.631 --> 01:41:21.426
<i>in the road to justice
and recovery.</i>

01:41:23.762 --> 01:41:25.263
I personally...

01:41:27.640 --> 01:41:29.768
don't believe
in capital punishment.

01:41:32.604 --> 01:41:33.897
I do believe...

01:41:34.981 --> 01:41:37.650
in the rights of the victims.

01:41:39.402 --> 01:41:40.904
<i>I do believe...</i>

01:41:41.946 --> 01:41:44.366
<i>that they deserve recompense.</i>

01:41:44.616 --> 01:41:49.662
<i>No matter how significant
or insignificant it may be...</i>

01:41:50.038 --> 01:41:52.499
in comparison
to the loss suffered.

01:41:55.168 --> 01:41:57.253
I've suffered such a loss.

01:41:59.172 --> 01:42:01.508
And like some of you here...

01:42:02.384 --> 01:42:05.136
I've spent
those sleepless nights...

01:42:06.888 --> 01:42:08.932
trying desperately to...

01:42:10.517 --> 01:42:14.312
squelch down that
bullish instinct for revenge.

01:42:17.565 --> 01:42:19.943
<i>And I have wondered...</i>

01:42:20.276 --> 01:42:22.487
<i>Jack, look at me.
Look at the kite.</i>

01:42:23.363 --> 01:42:24.864
<i>If this pain will...</i>

01:42:26.157 --> 01:42:29.035
<i>- ever abate.
- Smile!</i>

01:42:30.745 --> 01:42:32.205
<i>I've learnt...</i>

01:42:33.289 --> 01:42:37.335
<i>that time does not heal
the wound.</i>

01:42:38.503 --> 01:42:41.214
<i>It will though, in its most...</i>

01:42:42.716 --> 01:42:44.592
merciful way...

01:42:48.054 --> 01:42:50.432
plant the edge ever so slightly.

01:42:57.605 --> 01:42:58.940
So...

